cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.AI 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with the unsupervised discovery of linguistic structure from raw speech data. It may also belong to cs.SD (Sound) because it deals with acoustic patterns in speech. Additionally, it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) because it proposes an approach for automatic learning of models and parameters. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) because it deals with the automatic discovery of linguistic structure.
